description.displayText: Benna helped us out of a bind last minute when another provider cancelled. She was communicative, punctual, and kind. She took care of our 15 month old baby and was not flustered by our hyperactive, needy pup. We will definitely try to hire her again next time!

description.displayText: Benna started with us as a temporarily nanny when my son was 6 months old and we were lucky enough to have her help us full time for 3.5 years!  She cared for my toddler and then infant, doing everything the kids needed as my husband and I both work full time.  Benna kept the kids engaged with art projects, music, outdoor/indoor play, day outings - and taught them so much.  Benna 'lived-in' with us the last two years and we will be forever grateful to her for getting us through COVID!  Benna is reliable, trustworthy, fun and I highly recommend her to other families looking for care!

description.displayText: We hired Benna when visiting NYC for a couple of days. She watched our 14-month old daughter in our hotel room and put her to bed. It was our first time using a non-family member as a babysitter (outside of day care), but when I first spoke to Benna on the phone I could tell she was caring, reliable, and very experienced.  She also put me at ease when she arrived and quickly bonded with our daughter.  After we left, she kept me updated and soothed our daughter to sleep.  Benna was wonderful. I wish we lived closer so we could use her more frequently, but I would definitely hire her the next time we are in town and I would highly recommend her.

description.displayText: Benna is terrific. She's done date night babysitting for us several times (infant <1 year old) and cat sat during the holidays. She's always punctual and can be available at the last minute. When she arrives and we debrief about how our baby is doing, she listens carefully and asks good questions so that she is well prepared for the evening. Personally she is very sweet, caring, and patient. We've recommended Benna to several of our friends and will definitely be hiring her again in the future.

description.displayText: Benna has babysat our 2 year old son a few times and she is really great with him. She's always on time and joins in playing with him right away to help give us a tear less goodbye. We mentioned our son liked music and she made a point to have some music time with him. She sticks to our bedtime routine and fills us in when we get home. Its great having such a dedicated and patient sitter like Benna. We'll definitely call her again.

description.displayText: Benna has babysat my son since he was 2 (he is now 5). He loves her dearly and they always have a lot of fun together. Benna has a lot of energy, which is great with a little boy, and is very dependable and trustworthy -- my son has a number of severe food allergies, and I always feel that he is safe with her. I definitely recommend her!

description.displayText: Benna cared for my 2 year old son for a year.  Not only was she always reliable and on-time, she took immense joy in being with my son.  Their days together were filled with activities that provided him with much stimulation and joy.

description.displayText: Benna has been great.  Dependable, awesome with our 2 yr old daughter, and fun.  We will hire her again and again.

description.displayText: I cannot say enough wonderful things about Benna. She was unbelievable with our son right from the start. He was just two months old and from the minute she met him she was warm, caring and completely connected which is not always easy with a baby that young. She made sure that he was engaged during the day and always checked in with us about the kinds of things they did. She deferred to us about schedule, etc., but also gave us a little gentle needed guidance which we appreciated, and only did so when she saw that we asked for it.  Our son also needed a little early physical therapy and she was amazing about learning what to do and being sure she did his exercises during the day. On top of all of that, our 3 1/2 year old daughter asked every day if she would be able to see Benna before she left, and she had hardly even met her. We knew that we would only need to hire someone for a few months, but still really wanted to hire a full time babysitter that we could really create a relationship with and never could have imagined that we would be as fortunate as we were in finding Benna.
